es.at(name_);\n            auto init_is_word = false;\n            auto is_word = false;","numLines":50,"startLine":2340,"totalLines":3408}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ERo2f31JFwEzdMsAazNtLX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a clear picture of the bug. Let me confirm the exact logic:\n\nThe bug is in `LinkReferences::visit(Reference& ope)` at line 2500-2504. When a macro parameter name (e.g., `D`) collides with a global rule name (also `D`), the code:\n1. Correctly sets `found_param = true` and `ope.iarg_ = i` (marking it as a macro parameter)\n2. But then **unconditionally** also sets `ope.rule_ = &rule` when the name exists in the grammar\n\nThen in `Reference::parse` (line 2348), the check `if (rule_)` runs first — so when `D` appears inside the body of macro `B(D)`, it has both `iarg_` set (correct: parameter) and `rule_` set (wrong: global rule `D`). The `if (rule_)` branch wins, so it calls the global rule `D` (matching `'d'`) instead of the macro parameter (which should be `C`, matching `'c'`).\n\n---\n\nROOT CAUSE: `peglib.h:2500-2504` — In `LinkReferences::visit`, when a reference name matches both a macro parameter and a global grammar rule, `ope.rule_` is set unconditionally even though the reference is a macro parameter. `Reference::parse` checks `rule_` first (line 2348), so the global rule takes priority over the macro parameter, causing the parameter to be silently ignored and the global same-named rule to be called instead.\n\nLOCAL FIX: Add a guard so `ope.rule_` is only set when the reference is **not** a macro parameter:\n```cpp\n// Before (line 2500-2504):\nif (grammar_.count(ope.name_)) {\n    auto& rule = grammar_.at(ope.name_);\n    ope.rule_ = &rule;\n}\n\n// After:\nif (!found_param && grammar_.count(ope.name_)) {\n    auto& rule = grammar_.at(ope.name_);\n    ope.rule_ = &rule;\n}\n```\n\nGLOBAL FIX: Enforce a hygiene rule at grammar-validation time (in `ReferenceChecker`) that macro parameter names must not shadow any top-level grammar rule names — emit a compile-time error (or at minimum a warning) whenever a parameter identifier collides with a defined rule. This eliminates the entire class of silent shadowing bugs by making the ambiguity a parse-time error rather than leaving it to runtime precedence between `rule_` and `iarg_`, which is fragile and order-dependent."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1224,"cache_read_input_tokens":26542,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1224},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7007705-6449-4a1c-9631-ae2adc6d93b5","uuid":"f33333c4-2ebf-49c4-b0d9-be68deec583f"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":40522,"duration_api_ms":41384,"num_turns":8,"result":"I now have a clear picture of the bug. Let me confirm the exact logic:\n\nThe bug is in `LinkReferences::visit(Reference& ope)` at line 2500-2504. When a macro parameter name (e.g., `D`) collides with a global rule name (also `D`), the code:\n1. Correctly sets `found_param = true` and `ope.iarg_ = i` (marking it as a macro parameter)\n2. But then **unconditionally** also sets `ope.rule_ = &rule` when the name exists in the grammar\n\nThen in `Reference::parse` (line 2348), the check `if (rule_)` runs first — so when `D` appears inside the body of macro `B(D)`, it has both `iarg_` set (correct: parameter) and `rule_` set (wrong: global rule `D`). The `if (rule_)` branch wins, so it calls the global rule `D` (matching `'d'`) instead of the macro parameter (which should be `C`, matching `'c'`).\n\n---\n\nROOT CAUSE: `peglib.h:2500-2504` — In `LinkReferences::visit`, when a reference name matches both a macro parameter and a global grammar rule, `ope.rule_` is set unconditionally even though the reference is a macro parameter. `Reference::parse` checks `rule_` first (line 2348), so the global rule takes priority over the macro parameter, causing the parameter to be silently ignored and the global same-named rule to be called instead.\n\nLOCAL FIX: Add a guard so `ope.rule_` is only set when the reference is **not** a macro parameter:\n```cpp\n// Before (line 2500-2504):\nif (grammar_.count(ope.name_)) {\n    auto& rule = grammar_.at(ope.name_);\n    ope.rule_ = &rule;\n}\n\n// After:\nif (!found_param && grammar_.count(ope.name_)) {\n    auto& rule = grammar_.at(ope.name_);\n    ope.rule_ = &rule;\n}\n```\n\nGLOBAL FIX: Enforce a hygiene rule at grammar-validation time (in `ReferenceChecker`) that macro parameter names must not shadow any top-level grammar rule names — emit a compile-time error (or at minimum a warning) whenever a parameter identifier collides with a defined rule. This eliminates the entire class of silent shadowing bugs by making the ambiguity a parse-time error rather than leaving it to runtime precedence between `rule_` and `iarg_`, which is fragile and order-dependent.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"b7007705-6449-4a1c-9631-ae2adc6d93b5","total_cost_usd":0.14099865,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":15953,"cache_read_input_tokens":150063,"output_tokens":2339,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":15953,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":625,"cache_read_input_tokens":26542,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1224,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1224},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":962,"outputTokens":17,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.001047,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":8,"outputTokens":2339,"cacheReadInputTokens":150063,"cacheCreationInputTokens":15953,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.13995165,"contextWindow":400000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"8b8453ff-05ab-49d4-9380-8f8446ffe804"}
